3. `(nth_partial i <| nth_partial j f) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`: This is the `i`-th partial derivative of the `j`-th partial derivative of `f`, evaluated at the point `(1 - t) • x + t • y`. Let's denote this as `f''_{ij}(t)`.

